decks.notes: The main focus of this deck is to quickly deal damage to the opponent by utilizing low-cost spells and creatures. It aims to overwhelm the opponent by constantly applying pressure and finishing them off before they have a chance to stabilize. The deck includes a mix of burn spells and aggressive creatures like Monastery Swiftspear, Goblin Guide, and Eidolon of the Great Revel to maximize damage output. This deck is designed to be fast-paced and relentless, aiming to win the game swiftly through direct damage.

The main concept of this Bant Control deck is to stall out the game and control the board using a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and powerful planeswalkers. The deck utilizes cards like Path to Exile, Mana Leak, and Force of Negation to disrupt the opponent's game plan, while also generating card advantage with Mystic Sanctuary and Archmage's Charm. The deck also includes powerful win conditions in Uro, Titan of Nature's Wrath and Teferi, Hero of Dominaria, allowing the player to take over the game once they've gained control.

The main focus of this deck is to control the board by utilizing cards like Cryptic Command and Metallic Rebuke, while also generating value through cards like Mishra's Bauble and Arcum's Astrolabe. The deck also aims to ramp up with cards like Urza, Lord High Artificer and Uro, Titan of Nature's Wrath. Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Wrenn and Six provide additional value and recursion for the deck. The combination of control elements, value generation, and ramp make this deck a potent force in the Modern format.

The main concept of this deck is to disrupt opponents' mana bases with Magus of the Moon and Pillage while ramping up your own mana with Utopia Sprawl and Arbor Elf. Seasoned Pyromancer and Chandra, Torch of Defiance provide card advantage and additional threats, while Klothys, God of Destiny helps to control the graveyard and gain life. The creatures like Glorybringer and Bloodbraid Elf provide powerful attacks and board presence, with some removal options like Lightning Bolt and Bonecrusher Giant. The deck aims to control the board and outvalue the opponent in the mid to late game.

The main goal of this deck is to quickly fill up the graveyard with key cards like Stinkweed Imp, Narcomoeba, and Golgari Thug using cards like Cathartic Reunion and Life from the Loam. Utilizing the dredge mechanic, the deck aims to constantly bring back creatures like Bloodghast and Prized Amalgam from the graveyard for constant pressure. Combining this with cards like Conflagrate and Ox of Agonas for additional reach and disruption, the deck looks to overwhelm opponents with a fast and consistent graveyard synergy to secure victory.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by using a combination of removal spells, hand disruption, and versatile instant and sorcery spells. The inclusion of Niv-Mizzet Reborn as the win condition allows the player to consistently draw cards and gain card advantage, while also providing a powerful threat on the battlefield. The mana base is carefully constructed to ensure that all five colors are easily accessible, enabling the player to cast a wide variety of spells and adapt to any situation.

The deck focuses on assembling a powerful combo utilizing Underworld Breach, Grinding Station, and Mishra's Bauble to quickly mill through the library. Emry and Urza provide additional synergy and card advantage to generate the necessary resources for the combo. Cryptic Command and Metallic Rebuke are used for interaction and protection, while Thassa's Oracle acts as a win condition. The deck seeks to efficiently manipulate the graveyard and the library to set up the combo and win the game in a decisive manner.

This deck focuses on quickly generating a wide board presence of aggressive goblin creatures through cards like Aether Vial and Skirk Prospector, while maximizing the synergy between goblins with cards like Grumgully, the Generous and Metallic Mimic. The deck utilizes key cards like Goblin Ringleader and Goblin Matron to maintain card advantage and tutor for needed cards. Additionally, the deck includes disruptive elements like Munitions Expert and Sling-Gang Lieutenant to control the board and close out games efficiently. The efficient mana base allows for consistent and explosive plays to overwhelm the opponent.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by utilizing powerful planeswalkers like Jace, the Mind Sculptor and Teferi, Hero of Dominaria, along with disruptive counterspells like Cryptic Command and Force of Negation. The deck also uses efficient removal spells like Path to Exile and Supreme Verdict to deal with threats while generating card advantage with cards like Uro, Titan of Nature's Wrath. The deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents through card advantage and board control, ultimately grinding them out for the win.

The deck revolves around using small, evasive creatures like Blighted Agent and Glistener Elf to quickly deal poison counters to the opponent. By utilizing pump spells such as Mutagenic Growth, Might of Old Krosa, and Scale Up, these creatures can become lethal threats in just a few turns. Protection spells like Vines of Vastwood and Blossoming Defense help to keep your creatures safe from removal. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with infect damage before they have a chance to stabilize, ultimately winning the game through poison counters instead of traditional combat damage.

This Eldrazi Aggro deck focuses on ramping up mana quickly with the Eldrazi Temple lands and Urza's lands to play large threats like Karn, the Great Creator, Reality Smasher, and Thought-Knot Seer. The deck also includes disruption like Chalice of the Void and Mind Stone to control the board. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with powerful creatures and utilize utility lands like Ghost Quarter and Blast Zone to maintain control of the game.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through a combination of powerful planeswalkers, efficient card draw, and versatile counterspells. By utilizing cards like Jace, Teferi, and Uro, the deck aims to outvalue the opponent and gain incremental advantages over time. With a mix of removal spells like Path to Exile and board wipes like Supreme Verdict, it is able to disrupt the opponent's game plan while setting up its own win condition. The mana base is optimized for consistency and versatility, allowing for a wide range of plays depending on the situation.

The main concept of this deck is to control the game by utilizing a combination of powerful control spells and aggressive creatures to disrupt the opponent's game plan. By ramping up mana with cards like Arbor Elf and Utopia Sprawl, the deck is able to quickly deploy threats like Bloodbraid Elf and Glorybringer. Magus of the Moon punishes opponents for running non-basic lands, while cards like Pillage and Lightning Bolt provide removal and disruption. Klothys, God of Destiny provides additional value and life gain. Overall, the deck aims to control the board and pressure the opponent to secure a victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing Spirits with abilities that protect each other and disrupt the opponent's game plan. Cards like Drogskol Captain and Supreme Phantom boost the power of Spirits, while Spell Queller and Deputy of Detention help control the board. Aether Vial allows for quick creature deployment, while Path to Exile deals with threats. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive creature strategy, protecting its own creatures and disrupting the opponent's plans along the way.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly fill the graveyard with cards like Bloodghast, Narcomoeba, and Stinkweed Imp, using cards like Cathartic Reunion and Life from the Loam. By doing so, it aims to bring back multiple creatures from the graveyard at once with Prized Amalgam and trigger their abilities, such as Creeping Chill to deal damage to the opponent. The deck also utilizes cards like Ox of Agonas to refill the hand and keep the combo going, eventually overwhelming the opponent with an army of creatures and burn damage.

This Jund Aggro deck focuses on disruption and aggression, using a mix of hand disruption spells like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek to control the opponent's hand while deploying threats like Tarmogoyf, Bloodbraid Elf, and Kroxa, Titan of Death's Hunger to apply pressure and close out the game quickly. The deck also utilizes powerful planeswalkers like Liliana of the Veil and Wrenn and Six to generate value and control the board. With a versatile removal suite including Lightning Bolt, Fatal Push, and Assassin's Trophy, this deck aims to overwhelm opponents with efficient threats and disruption.
